    }

    // The maximum number of special indices we can achieve is floor((n-2)/2).
    // This is because a special index i requires i-1 and i+1 to be smaller than nums[i].
    // If we aim for a sequence of peaks: L, P1, L', P2, L'', ...
    // P1 requires L < P1 > L'. P2 requires L' < P2 > L''.
    // If we space them out, e.g., P1 at index i, P2 at index j, we need |i-j| >= 3 for them to be independent 
